Ecosphere Technologies, Jean Michel Cousteau, and SolarCity to help solve the World's Water and Energy Crisis with Revolutionary New Solar Product | Business Wire


























































Ecosphere Technologies, Jean Michel Cousteau, and SolarCity to help 
      solve the World's Water and Energy Crisis with Revolutionary New Solar 
      Product












Download



Full Size


Small


Preview


Thumbnail










Ecosphere Technologies, Inc. announces revolutionary new solar product
with the introduction of the Ecos Power Cube.  (Photo: Business Wire)





December 11, 2006 10:04 AM Eastern Standard Time



STUART, Fla.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Ecosphere Technologies, Inc. (OTC BB: ESPH), the Stuart, Florida-based 
      company that creates engineered and patented Clean Tech solutions that 
      address pressing global environmental and humanitarian issues, today 
      announced that its mission to help solve the world water and energy 
      crisis can be realized with the introduction of the Ecos Power Cube (see 
      attached photo).
    


      "This important all-solar product from Ecosphere Technologies signals 
      that the Clean Tech marketplace may be the perfect fusion of commerce 
      and sustainability," indicated the leading futurist and author Dr. James 
      Canton, CEO & Chairman, Institute for Global Futures, and member of 
      Ecosphere Technologies Advisory Board. "This break-through is just what 
      the world needs now to build a prosperous and clean energy future for 
      all of humanity in the 21st century."
    

      Ecosphere’s CEO Dennis McGuire stated, “On 
      the banks of the Hudson River in 2005 Jean Michel Cousteau challenged 
      Ecosphere Technologies to create a high volume low cost water filtration 
      system that only uses the power of the sun to create electricity and 
      purify water for remote villages and third world countries. Ecosphere 
      accepted the challenge and designed the Ecos Power Cube. Ecosphere 
      Technologies will introduce this revolutionary new water filtration and 
      energy product through a newly formed subsidiary division called 
      Ecosphere Energy Solutions, Inc. The market for solar products in 2005 
      was $11 billion and the market is expected to grow to $51 billion by 
      2015. We expect this exciting new product will be well received by this 
      growing market. Ecosphere Technologies is a portal for Clean Tech 
      solutions and this is just another example of our commitment to the 
      future of the planet and our shareholders. “


      Jean Michel Cousteau, Ecosphere spokesperson, ocean pioneer and 
      environmentalist has been an ambassador and advocate to bring awareness 
      to the world water crisis since his speech at the Water For Peace Forum 
      in Kyoto in 2003. At that forum Cousteau urged policymakers to enlist 
      the private sector, which profits from water-related products, to use 
      part of their gains to help guarantee clean water for those in need. 
      Cousteau now states “Raising awareness of the 
      world water crisis was the first step in solving a problem of such 
      magnitude. The final step is for companies to provide a sustainable low 
      cost technical solution that works. The Ecos Power Cube is revolutionary 
      in the fact that it will use only the power of the sun to create and 
      store the energy needed to run water filtration components, pumps, or 
      motors. It is a perpetual motion water and electrical system that uses 
      no fossil fuels. The Ecos Power Cube can be used to provide water and 
      electricity for a small village. Multiple systems could be used 
      throughout a village to power its school, water system, buildings, and 
      communications systems. I am very proud to have been associated with 
      Ecosphere Technologies over the past 8 years and have witnessed their 
      continued commitment to protecting the people of our planet and its eco 
      systems with their Clean Tech solutions.”


      Lyndon Rive CEO of SolarCity stated. “We are 
      very excited and committed to working with Jean Michel Cousteau and 
      Ecosphere to help solve the worlds water and energy crisis. The Ecos 
      Power Cube will allow people all over the world access to clean water 
      and portable energy.”


      About Ecosphere Technologies:
    

      Ecosphere creates engineered and patented Clean Tech solutions that 
      address pressing global environmental and humanitarian issues. The 
      Company has developed products that reduce the discharge of contaminated 
      residue into the air, oceans and other water systems, as well as 
      products that purify water through unique mobile systems that can 
      operate independently throughout the world. Our intellectual property 
      includes a portfolio of registered and pending patents, trade secrets, 
      trademarks, and copyrights. Ecosphere has ten registered United States 
      patents all relating to robotic coating removal technology, airplane and 
      automotive paint removal technology. Ecosphere has filed three United 
      States patent applications relating to our water filtration system. In 
      addition, the Company has 411 patent applications pending either actual 
      filings or reserved under the right to seek priority date filing 
      covering our robotic coating removal technology and automotive paint 
      removal technology in numerous countries, including Europe, Asia, and 
      the rest of the world. Additional information is available at www.Ecospheretech.com.
    

      To be included in Ecosphere's email list click below: http://www.b2i.us/irpass.asp?BzID=1368&to=ea&s=0


      About Jean Michel Cousteau and Ocean Futures Society
    

      The mission of Cousteau's Ocean Futures Society is to explore our global 
      ocean, inspire and educate people throughout the world to act 
      responsibly for its protection, documenting the critical connection 
      between humanity and nature, and celebrating the ocean's vital 
      importance to the survival of all life on our planet. Ocean Futures 
      Society is based in Santa Barbara, CA., USA, with offices in Paris, 
      France and Washington DC. For more information about the endeavors of 
      Ocean Futures Society and Jean-Michel Cousteau, visit their website at www.oceanfutures.org


      About SolarCity
    

      Founded in 2006, SolarCity matches advanced solar power technology with 
      a suite of installation services. The company’s 
      comprehensive offering removes the technical, regulatory, and financing 
      barriers to solar power, helping customers make smart alternative energy 
      choices that save money. Boasting a team with more than 20 years of 
      experience in solar systems design and installation, and a proven track 
      record of bringing new technologies to market, SolarCity is uniquely 
      positioned to make solar power a practical choice for everyone. www.solarcity.com


      About Dr. James Canton and the Institute for Global Futures
    

      Dr. Canton is Chairman and CEO of the Institute for Global Futures, an 
      internationally-recognized San Francisco-based think tank he founded in 
      1990, to help clients better anticipate the future. Dr. Canton advises 
      Fortune 1000 corporations and governments worldwide. Dr Canton advises 
      the National Science Foundation and is a Senior Fellow at the Kellogg 
      Innovation Network at Northwestern University’s 
      Kellogg School of Management and sits on the Research Visionary Advisory 
      Board for Motorola. Dr. Canton also sat on the Advisory Board of MIT’s 
      Media Lab, Europe and advised the White House’s 
      Office of Science and Technology.
    

http://www.futureguru.com/about.php


      This press release contains forward-looking statements within the 
      meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995 (the 
      "Act"), including, but not limited to, the expected market for solar 
      products and the attraction of that market to Ecosphere’s 
      new product. Additionally, words such as "seek," "intend," "believe," 
      "plan," "estimate," "expect," "anticipate" and other similar expressions 
      are forward-looking statements within the meaning of the Act. Some or 
      all of the events or results anticipated by these forward- looking 
      statements may not occur. Factors that could cause or contribute to such 
      differences include worldwide economic conditions, Ecosphere obtaining 
      the financing needed to produce this new product and manufacture working 
      models on a cost effective basis Further information on the Company's 
      risk factors is contained in its Form 10-KSB and other reports filed 
      with the Securities and Exchange Commission. Ecosphere does not 
      undertake any duty nor does it intend to update the results of these 
      forward-looking statements.
    


